1. Clone the repo
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone git@github.com:robsok/content_pipeline.git
cd content_pipeline
2. Create & activate your virtual environment
Linux / WSL / macOS

bash
Copy
Edit
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Windows (PowerShell)

powershell
Copy
Edit
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\Activate
3. Install dependencies
bash
Copy
Edit
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
(If you don’t yet have a requirements.txt, run pip freeze > requirements.txt now while your current environment is working so it’s ready for the next clean start.)

4. Run your app / scripts

